In consultation with the State Advisory Council on Hereditary and Congenital Disorders, the Department shall:
Establish protocols for a health care provider to obtain and deliver test specimens to the Department's public health laboratory;
Determine the screening tests that the Department's public health laboratory is required to perform;
Maintain a coordinated statewide system for newborn screening that carries out the purpose described in subsection (c) of this section that includes:
Communicating the results of screening tests to the health care provider of the newborn infant;
Locating newborn infants with abnormal test results;
Sharing newborn screening information between hospitals, health care providers, treatment centers, and laboratory personnel; and
Delivering needed clinical, diagnostic, and treatment information to health care providers, parents, and caregivers; and
Adopt regulations that set forth the standards and requirements for newborn screening for hereditary and congenital disorders that are required under this subtitle, including:
Performing newborn screening tests;
Coordinating the reporting, follow-up, and treatment activities with parents, caregivers, and health care providers; and
Establishing fees for newborn screening that do not exceed an amount sufficient to cover the administrative, laboratory, and follow-up costs associated with the performance of screening tests under this subtitle.
